FAROESE WEATHER BULLETIN FM DMI ISSUED AT 1950 UTC (WIND FORCE IN M/S)
WEATHER SUMMARY:
A LOW 999 HPA BETWEEN CAPE FAREWELL AND ICELAND IS ALMOST STNR AND GIVES
A WEAK S- AND SOUTHWESTERN FLOW OF COOL BUT MOIST AIR WITH SCT SHWRS OVER
FAROES AND THERE IS RISK OF LOC FOG. LATE WEDNESDAY A MINOR LOW 1003 HPA
REACHES FAROES FM SSW TOGETHER WITH THE ASSOCIATED FRONT WITH RAIN AND SHWRS.
